l%20Assembly%20can%20suggest%20that%20different%20actions%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20truce%2C%20cease-fire%20or%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0be%20taken%20during%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-hamas-war-israel-expands-ground-operations-into-gaza%2Flive-67228509%5C%22%3Estate%20of%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20many%20of%20these%20terms%20are%20often%20used%20interchangeably%2C%20each%20have%20different%20political%20implications%20and%20legal%20meanings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECalls%20made%20by%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20are%20ultimately%20merely%C2%A0suggestions%20to%20actors%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-at-war%2Ft-57547294%5C%22%3Ewar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20unlike%20decisions%20made%20by%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%2C%20they%C2%A0are%20not%20legally%20binding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20are%2C%20however%2C%20considered%20powerful%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20reflect%20the%20general%20will%20of%20UN%20member%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20an%20explanation%20of%20the%20differences%20between%20the%20various%C2%A0methods%20of%20action%20suggested%20by%20UN%20bodies%20during%20times%20of%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETruce%20(%E2%80%8B%E2%80%8Bsuspension%20of%20hostilities)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20truce%20is%20not%C2%A0binding%2C%20it%20just%20indicates%20a%20halt%20in%20fighting.%20Truce%20agreements%20are%C2%A0made%20by%20belligerents%20themselves.%20A%20truce%20can%20take%20place%20in%20one%20specific%20geographic%20area%20of%20a%20broader%20conflict.%20These%20agreements%20can%20come%20and%20go%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20conflict%20and%20do%20not%20indicate%20the%20state%20of%20war%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Committee%20of%20the%20Red%20Cross%20(ICRC)%20uses%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Ctruce%E2%80%9D%C2%A0interchangeably%20with%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Csuspension%20of%20hostilities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20ICRC%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20truce%20should%20enable%20work%20to%20be%20done%20that%20is%20unrelated%20to%20the%20general%20conduct%20of%20war%20(e.g.%20removal%20of%20the%20wounded%2C%20burial%20of%20the%20dead%2C%20exchange%20of%20prisoners)%20or%20give%20military%20commanders%20time%20to%20ask%20for%20instructions%20regarding%20negotiations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%2C%20a%20truce%20can%20be%20called%20for%20any%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20not%20restricted%20to%20humanitarian%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECessation%20of%20hostilities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20call%20for%20a%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20is%20considered%20more%20formal%20than%20a%20truce%2C%20but%20unlike%20a%20cease-fire%2C%20it%20is%20nonbinding.%20A%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20means%20one%20or%20both%20sides%20have%20announced%20plans%20to%20suspend%20fighting.%20These%20can%20indicate%20the%20beginning%20of%20broader%20peace%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHumanitarian%20pause%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20Office%20for%20the%20Coordination%20of%20Humanitarian%20Affairs%20(OCHA)%2C%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%20is%20considered%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctemporary%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20purely%20for%20humanitarian%20purposes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20pauses%20are%20usually%20negotiated%20to%20take%20place%20for%20a%20defined%20period%20of%20time%2C%20sometimes%20only%20over%20a%20few%20hours%2C%20and%20in%20a%20specific%20geographic%20area%20where%20humanitarian%20activities%20are%20planned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECease-fire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20declarations%20of%20a%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20or%20a%20truce%2C%20a%20cease-fire%20is%20generally%20meant%20to%20be%20binding.%20Like%20a%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20or%20truce%2C%20it%20is%20only%20temporary%20in%20nature%2C%20but%20is%20generally%20expected%20to%20last%20for%20a%20longer%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECease-fires%20do%20not%20announce%20the%20end%20of%20a%20conflict%2C%20but%20they%20are%20meant%20to%20put%20the%20opposing%20parties%20in%20communication%20with%20one%20another%20about%20potential%20permanent%20settlements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20truce%2C%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%20or%20a%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%2C%20the%20declaration%20of%20a%20cease-fire%20often%20applies%20to%20the%20entire%20geographical%20area%20of%20a%20conflict%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UN.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArmistice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20armistice%20indicates%20the%20formal%20end%20to%20a%20war%20negotiated%20by%20the%20involved%20parties%2C%20but%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20peace%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDays%20of%20tranquility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESometimes%20in%20a%20state%20of%20conflict%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Fund%20(UNICEF)%20and%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20will%20call%20for%20parties%20to%20a%20conflict%20to%20agree%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cday%20of%20tranquility.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20days%20are%20generally%20meant%20to%20give%20children%20uninterrupted%20access%20to%20health%20care%20on%20specific%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcease-fire-truce-armistice-whats-the-difference%2Fa-67243219%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698629404000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27104536%2FIsrael-tank-near-Gaza-border.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcease-fire-truce-armistice-whats-the-difference%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Three%20weeks%20into%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%20has%2