ut%20hydrogen%20typically%20needed%20to%20be%20produced%20in%20a%20lab%20using%20energy-intensive%20methods.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhite%20hydrogen%2C%20a%20newly%20identified%20hydrogen%20source%2C%20could%20eliminate%20the%20need%20for%20lab%20production.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20scientists%20in%20France%20have%20discovered%20what%20may%20be%20the%20largest%20known%20deposit%20of%20a%20clean%20energy%20resource%20that%20could%20be%20a%20saving%20grace%20in%20mitigating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fclimate-change%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacques%20Pironon%20and%20Phillipe%20De%20Donato%2C%20directors%20of%20research%20at%20France's%20National%20Centre%20of%20Scientific%20Research%2C%20found%20a%20deposit%20between%206%20million%20to%20250%20million%20metric%20tons%20of%20white%20hydrogen%2C%20or%20naturally%20occurring%20hydrogen%20gas%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F10%2F29%2Fclimate%2Fwhite-hydrogen-fossil-fuels-climate%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20hydrogen%20is%20relatively%20new%20to%20scientists.%20A%20study%20in%202018%20that%20analyzed%20a%20well%20in%20Mali%20producing%2098%25%20hydrogen%20gas%20brought%20the%20resource%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20scientific%20community%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20researchers%20across%20the%20globe%20are%20interested%20in%20white%20hydrogen%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20could%20help%20us%20%26quot%3Bget%20to%20speed%26quot%3B%20on%20saving%20the%20world%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fclimate-change%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20geochemist%20Viacheslav%20Zgonnik%20told%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20white%20hydrogen%20and%20why%20is%20it%20special%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHydrogen%20energy%20is%20not%20a%20new%20idea%20%E2%80%94%20it%20only%20produces%20water%20when%20burned%2C%20making%20it%20an%20environment-friendly%20energy%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20until%20recently%2C%20scientists%20thought%20mass%20amounts%20could%20only%20be%20produced%20in%20a%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20had%20asked%20me%20four%20years%20ago%20what%20I%20thought%20about%20natural%20hydrogen%2C%20I%20would%20have%20told%20you%2C%20'Oh%2C%20it%20doesn't%20exist%2C'%26quot%3B%20Geoffrey%20Ellis%2C%20a%20geochemist%20with%20the%20US%20Geological%20Survey%2C%20told%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20turns%20out%2C%20Ellis%20would've%20been%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20hydrogen%20refers%20to%20naturally%20occurring%20hydrogen.%20Its%20%26quot%3Bcolor%26quot%3B%20indicates%20its%20origin%3A%20it%20is%20naturally%20produced%20in%20the%20Earth's%20crust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20%26quot%3Bshades%26quot%3B%20of%20hydrogen%20are%20produced%20in%20a%20lab.%20They%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhydrogen-energy-help-climate-crisis-but-still-hurdles-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreen%20hydrogen%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20made%20from%20electrolysis%2C%20the%20process%20of%20splitting%20water%20into%20hydrogen%20and%20oxygen%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20gray%20hydrogen%2C%20which%20is%20made%20from%20methane%20gas%2C%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20hydrogen%20is%20the%20most%20abundant%20element%2C%20it%20is%20usually%20attached%20to%20other%20molecules%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0making%20the%20lab%20production%20process%20necessary.%20But%20separating%20hydrogen%20is%20energy-intensive%20and%20typically%20powered%20by%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it%20doesn't%20require%20any%20of%20these%20energy-intensive%20processes%2C%20climate%20experts%20say%20white%20hydrogen%20could%20be%20our%20saving%20grace%2C%20according%20to%20CNN.%20It's%20also%20cheaper%3A%20white%20hydrogen%20is%20estimated%20to%20cost%20about%20%241%20per%20kilogram%20to%20produce%2C%20while%20green%20hydrogen%20costs%20about%20%246%20per%20kilogram%2C%20per%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20start-ups%20are%20already%20exploring%20how%20to%20commercialize%20white%20hydrogen%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllis%20told%20CNN%20that%20speed%20is%20vital%20to%20ensure%20white%20hydrogen%20can%20help%20curb%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Zgonnik%20told%20CNN%20he's%20hopeful%20about%20the%20turnaround%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20all%20necessary%20technology%20we%20need%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewith%20some%20slight%20modifications%2C%26quot%3B%20Zgonnik%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20of%20the%20largest-known%20white%20hydrogen%20deposit%20yet%20comes%20just%20months%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fnews-release%2Fnasa-announces-summer-2023-hottest-on-record%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehottest%20summer%20on%20global%20record%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20to%20an%20end%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsummer-2023-heat-wave-tracker-temperature-records-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcerning%20milestone%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20climate%20researchers%20and%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-hydrogen-france-clean-energy-climate-change-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698613224000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653eb996356802a56be6f860%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-hydrogen-france-clean-energy-climate-change-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22White%20hydrogen%2C%20the%20newly%20discovered%20clean%20energy%20gas%2C%20could%20be%20key%20in%20mitigating%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20experts%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22khawkinson%40insid