ed%20it%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Blargest%20transformation%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20large%20public%20restaurant%20company%20in%20America%2C%20and%20it%20impacted%20several%20aspects%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpanera-bread-jobs-best-worst-parts-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPanera's%20business%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20from%20its%20loyalty%20program%20to%20its%20distribution%20channels.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20huge%20pressure%2C%20and%20things%20weren't%20going%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Shaich%20said%20in%20the%20interview%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20was%20dealing%20with%20activists%20%26quot%3Battacking%26quot%3B%20him%2C%20people%20dismissing%20his%20vision%2C%20and%20turnover%20in%20his%20executive%20ranks.%20And%20he%20said%20he%20remembers%20thinking%20to%20himself%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20god%2C%20it'd%20be%20just%20easier%20if%20I%20got%20hit%20by%20a%20truck.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShaich%20clarified%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20suicide%20wish%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20rather%20a%20function%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Boverwhelming%20sense%26quot%3B%20of%20responsibility%20he%20felt%20to%20people%20who%20were%20betting%20on%20him.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20pressure.%20That%20pressure%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20deliver%20for%20the%20good%20people%20that%20actually%20cared%20to%20believe%20in%20me%20in%20a%20world%20where%20nothing%20was%20actually%20certain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Shaich%20has%20also%20previously%20said%20he%20might%20have%20been%20too%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafter-26-years-as-ceo-of-a-huge-company-i-regret-not-firing-people-2018-2%3Fplatform%3Dhootsuite%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eobsessed%20with%20being%20a%20%26quot%3Bcaring%20leader.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShaich%20now%20seems%20to%20see%20challenging%20moments%20like%20this%20as%20a%20rite%20of%20passage.%20%26quot%3BBy%20the%20time%20you%20get%20to%2060%2C%20everyone%20gets%20knee-capped%20in%20some%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-who-didnt-find-success-until-later-in-life-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehe's%20turning%2070%20this%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20challenge%20is%20how%20you%20deal%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20Shaich%20said%20he%20found%20solace%20in%20his%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20day%20his%20CFO%20quit%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Shaich%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bpunch%20in%20the%20stomach%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20his%20daughter%20called%20him%20and%20asked%20him%20to%20put%20her%20to%20sleep%20because%20she%20had%20had%20a%20pretty%20tough%20day%2C%20too.%20Shaich%2C%20who%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fboston-travel-guide-hotels-activities-restaurants-and-more-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eworking%20from%20Boston%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20his%20family%20was%20vacationing%20in%20nearby%20Manchester%20at%20the%20time%2C%20said%20he%20was%20exhausted%20but%20still%20drove%20up%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20to%20see%20his%20daughter%20that%20night.%20As%20she%20was%20falling%20asleep%2C%20Shaich%20said%20he%20told%20her%20to%20relax%20and%20remember%20that%20when%20she%20woke%20up%20the%20next%20day%2C%20she'd%20feel%20different.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20new%20day%20and%20you%20just%20have%20to%20go%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20he%20told%20his%20daughter%20in%20the%20interview.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20was%20driving%20back%20to%20Boston%20that%20night%2C%20though%2C%20he%20said%20he%20realized%20that%20he%20hadn't%20just%20been%20talking%20to%20his%20daughter%20%E2%80%94%20he%20had%20been%20talking%20to%20himself%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20have%20to%20put%20one%20step%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20s