l%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20township%2C%20the%20company%20has%20launched%20412%20independent%20floors%20project%20'Windsong%20Residences'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftrident-realty-to-invest-rs-700-cr-to-build-independent-floors-at-panchkula-123102900517_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftrident-realty-to-invest-rs-700-cr-to-build-independent-floors-at-panchkula-123102900517_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftrident-realty-to-invest-rs-700-cr-to-build-independent-floors-at-panchkula-123102900517_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22South%20Africa%20Rugby%20World%20Cup%3A%20The%20Springboks%20give%20hope%20to%20a%20troubled%20nation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698578952000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F9B0F%2Fproduction%2F_131559693_gettyimages-1750469851.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67254346%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20South%20Africa%20faces%20economic%20troubles%20the%20Rugby%20World%20Cup%20success%20is%20a%20welcome%20distraction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A448%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67254346%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67254346.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67254346.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bahadur%20the%20Brave%20Shows%20How%20For%20Nepalese%20Migrant%20Workers%2C%20the%20Lockdown%20was%20Even%20More%20Difficult%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F29164548%2FBahadur-the-Brave-2023_02-768x417-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20too%20long%20ago%2C%20the%20Nepali%20security%20guard%20was%20a%20ubiquitous%20figure%20in%20a%20city%20like%20Mumbai%2C%20where%20almost%20every%20apartment%20complex%20employed%20a%20succession%20of%20men%20all%20called%20Bahadur.%20As%20if%20erasing%20their%20own%20identity%2C%20these%20Nepali%20men%2C%20when%20asked%20their%20name%2C%20invariably%20answered%20%E2%80%9CBahadur%E2%80%9D.%20They%20were%20hard-working%20and%20frugal%2C%20saving%20up%20their%20meagre%20earnings%20to%20take%20back%20to%20their%20families%20on%20their%20annual%C2%A0%20trip%20to%20their%20native%20villages%2C%20when%20they%20would%20be%20replaced%20by%20an%20incoming%20set%20of%20Bahadurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20more%20or%20less%20vanished%20from%20cities%20in%20western%20India%2C%20but%20in%20northern%20towns%20adjoining%20the%20Nepal%20border%2C%20they%20still%20come%20over%20for%20employment%20as%20casual%20labour%2C%20and%20it%20is%20this%20group%20of%20men%20that%20Diwa%20Shah%20has%20empathetically%20captured%20in%20her%20debut%20feature%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBahadur%20The%20Brave%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Set%20in%20Naintal%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20film%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20two%20Nepali%20friends%2C%20who%20have%20to%20make%20tough%20decisions%20about%20their%20future.%20The%20film%20won%20Shah%20the%20Kutxabank%20New%20Director%E2%80%99s%20Award%20at%20the%20San%20Sebastian%20Film%20Festival%20in%20Spain%20%E2%80%93%20a%20first%20for%20an%20Indian%20film%20%E2%80%93%20and%20is%20in%20competition%20at%20the%20ongoing%20Jio%20MAMI%20Film%20Festival.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20follows%20the%20somewhat%20simple-minded%20Hansi%20(Rupesh%20Lama)%2C%20who%20does%20odd%20jobs%20of%20fetching%20and%20carrying%20loads%20like%20sacks%20of%20grain%20and%20gas%20cylinders%20for%20the%20neighbouring%20shopkeepers%20and%20homemakers.%20When%20the%20coronavirus%20strikes%20and%20a%20strict%20lockdown%20is%20imposed%20in%20the%20hill%20town%2C%20Hansi%20finds%20ways%20of%20dodging%20the%20curfew%2C%20and%20it%20hurts%20when%20he%20is%20fined%20Rs%20500%20by%20the%20cops%20for%20not%20wearing%20a%20mask%20%E2%80%93%20money%20he%20has%20just%20scraped%20together%20by%20haggling%20with%20his%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHansi%E2%80%99s%20buddy%20and%20brother-in-law%2C%20Dil%20Bahadur%20(Rahul%20Mukhia)%2C%20takes%20advantage%20of%20the%20shortage%20of%20labour%20by%20accepting%20construction%20jobs.%20The%20lockdown%20is%20tough%20on%20them%20as%20their%20roommates%20start%20going%20back%20to%20Nepal%20one%20by%20one%2C%20and%20the%20few%20that%20remain%20are%20forced%20to%20stay%20indoors%2C%20playing%20cards%20and%20taking%20turns%20cooking%20meals.%20Their%20already%20hard-scrabble%20existence%20is%20made%20more%20difficult%20by%20unexpectedly%20cruel%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHansi%20gets%20news%20that%20his%20son%20who%20needs%20surgery%20for%20a%20stomach%20ailment%20has%20fallen%20down%20and%20broken%20his%20arm.%20But%20he%20is%20ashamed%20to%20go%20home%20without%20money.%20Every%20time%20Dil%20Bahadur%20makes%20arrangements%20for%20him%20to%20return%2C%C2%A0%20Hansi%20finds%20excuses%20to%20miss%20the%20bus.%20For%20a%20man%20who%20has%20trouble%20following%20basic%20conversations%20(his%20interactions%20with%20a%20kind%20housewife%20are%20hilarious)%2C%20Hansi%20also%20has%20hidden%20reserves%20of%20sly%20resourcefulness%20%E2%80%93%20like%20persuading%20a%20cop%20to%20lie%20to%20Dil%20Bahadur%20about%20the%20expiry%20of%20his%20travel%20permit%20so%20that%20he%20can%20avoid%20getting%20on%20the%20bus%20to%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20impasse%20is%20automatically%20broken%20when%20Hansi%20and%20Dil%20Bahadur%20steal%20some%20liquor%20from%20a%20warehouse%20and%20are%20caught%20on%20the%20CCTV%20camera.%20The%20boss%20accuses%20Dil%20Bahadur%20of%20also%20stealing%20money%20and%20threatens%20to%20call%20the%20cops.%C2%A0Hansi%20uses%20this%20incident%20to%20persuade%20Dil%20Bahadur%20to%20go%20back%2C%20promising%20to%20follow.%20Inadvertently%2C%20this%20innocent%20ploy%20results%20in%20tragedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMemories%20of%20lockdown%20coverage%20in%20print%20and%20TV%20enumerated%20the%20deaths%20of%20Indian%20migrant%20workers%20trying%20desperately%20to%20reach%20their%20families.%20Poor%20Nepali%20migrants%2C%20who%20were%20not%20even%20citizens%20of%20India%2C%20were%20trapped%20when%20the%20border%20was%20sealed.%20Hostile%20locals%20shouted%20slogans%20to%20exhort%20the%20Nepal%20government%20to%20take%20their%20citizens%20back.%20The%20migrants%20had%20to%20camp%20out%20in%20the%20cold%20at%20the%20border%2C%20with%20no%20money%20and%20no%20access%20to%20food%20or%20supplies.%20The%20governments%20on%20either%20side%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20care%20less%20about%20these%20powerless%20men%2C%20who%20had%20nothing%20to%20offer%20in%20return%20for%20safe%20passage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDiwa%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20the%20subject%20is%20understated%20but%20also%20deeply%20humane.%20She%20portrays%20the%20bleakness%20of%20the%20lives%20of%20these%20migrants%20against%20a%20backdrop%20of%20scenic%20beauty.%20There%20is%20some%20humour%20and%20joy%20even%20in%20a%20crisis%20when%20the%20group%20of%20workers%20get%20together.%20But%20a%20desperate%20Hansi%20is%20left%20to%20stew%20in%20guilt%20and%20helplessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20lead%20actors%20bring%20out%20the%20truth%20and%20realism%20of%20the%20story%20with%20their%20performances%3B%20the%20viewer%20cannot%20but%20sympathise%20with%20the%20plight%20of%20these%20Bahadurs%20trying%20to%20keep%20their%20families%20out%20of%20abject%20poverty.%20The%20film%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20the%20famed%20resilience%20of%20the%20poor%20comes%20at%20a%20steep%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepa%20Gahlot%20is%20a%20national%20award%20winning%20critic%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698578731000%2C%22visual%22%3A